('a4302e15-a964-57f8-ba74-9db47e3c1edc', '3c34dd5c-44f0-45cb-8f6b-3d138ddc03c9', 'The rapid advancement of ___ has sparked intense debate about whether machines will eventually surpass human cognitive abilities.', '___ 的快速進步引發了激烈的辯論：機器最終是否會超越人類的認知能力。', 'AI', 'VR', 'DNA', 'GPS', 'AI 是 Artificial Intelligence 的縮寫。Artificial 代表「人工的」，Intelligence 代表「智慧」。', '想像一個機器人 (Artificial) 擁有像人類一樣的大腦 (Intelligence)，這就是 AI。', '2026-07-06 19:21:16', '2026-07-06 19:21:16'),
('91121694-fe05-5416-a53c-4ed06c9d520c', '43af794d-1278-4d09-b593-70583b8fed01', 'The university offers several ___ courses for students who have already mastered the basics of computer science.', '這所大學為那些已經掌握電腦科學基礎的學生提供幾門高等課程。', 'advanced', 'ancient', 'shallow', 'nervous', 'ad- (向著) + vance (前進) → 向前移動的 → 先進的、高等的。', '記住 ad- 表示 ''to/towards''，vance 聯想到 advance (前進)，往前的發展就是「先進的」。', '2026-07-06 18:05:13', '2026-07-06 18:05:13'),
('8764e55b-f381-503f-9880-bd849f272cf0', 'af88ce9a-6ab0-4e90-aac8-2a374a0fbbf6', 'Many students experience high levels of ___ during final exam week due to the pressure of grades.', '由於成績的壓力，許多學生在期末考週會感到高度的焦慮。', 'anxiety', 'happiness', 'confidence', 'curiosity', 'anxi- 意指不安或焦慮。', '想像考試前緊張到手心冒汗、心跳加速的感覺 → anxiety (焦慮)。', '2026-07-06 21:58:53', '2026-07-06 21:58:53'),
('c9e1daa6-d93d-555b-99f3-a4ec5ef90d98', '1f79d1a1-d48d-4099-b1d2-5639ef2aea7f', 'The researchers observed an ___ using its powerful limbs to swing through the forest canopy.', '研究人員觀察到一隻大猩猩利用其強壯的四肢在森林林冠層間盪漾。', 'ape', 'eagle', 'eel', 'emu', 'ape 為名詞，指大猩猩或類人猿。', '記住 ape 是類人猿，牠們會用強壯的手臂在樹林間盪漾。', '2026-07-06 22:46:33', '2026-07-06 22:46:33'),
('f8c70452-e2c5-56f5-8dd1-4a094d1bd2e0', 'ad327958-b59b-4b48-a28a-b82d7cbdb616', 'The travel agency handled all the travel ___ , including flights and hotel bookings.', '旅行社處理了所有的旅遊安排，包括航班和飯店預訂。', 'arrangements', 'achievements', 'discoveries', 'decisions', 'arrange (安排) + -ment (名詞字尾) → 安排、準備工作。', 'range 有「範圍、系列」的意思，將事物排列在一定的範圍內 → arrangement (安排)。', '2026-07-07 00:09:40', '2026-07-07 00:09:40'),
('b37fa759-4ed3-5264-b0ad-f12582f6073c', '867c15c7-a311-4f16-8c1f-5ab8611bc223', 'The bus will ___ at the station soon.', '公車很快就會到達車站。', 'arrive', 'leave', 'sleep', 'sing', 'ad- (朝向) + rive (岸) → 到達岸邊 → 到達。', '想像船隻「到」達岸邊的樣子。', '2026-07-06 14:51:06', '2026-07-06 14:51:06'),
('cbc0ba53-3292-553c-87a5-9c97723b0c10', '2ffa7f29-3bda-4d6f-95b9-7457dd4a3815', 'The young athlete will ___ to break the world record during the upcoming Olympics.', '這位年輕的運動員將在即將到來的奧運會期間試圖打破世界紀錄。', 'attempt', 'refuse', 'decide', 'forget', 'att- (向) + tempt (試驗/測試) → 試圖', 'temptation (誘惑) 會讓你想要 attempt (嘗試) 去做某事。', '2026-07-07 02:09:45', '2026-07-07 02:09:45'),
('62d44ec1-3362-5aa5-a584-4e5a486217b4', '8f38c8e5-e6c6-458b-8db5-0703b70766a3', 'The smell of fresh bread from the ___ is wonderful.', '從那家麵包店傳來的現烤麵包香味非常棒。', 'bakery', 'library', 'museum', 'factory', 'bake (烘烤) + -ery (表示場所的字尾) → 烘烤的地方', 'bake (烤) + ery (地方) → 烤麵包的地方 → 麵包店', '2026-07-07 01:56:15', '2026-07-07 01:56:15'),
('feb85e7b-4790-5e7e-89a9-2be49016fba4', '470895bf-9e77-49fe-8d3c-695c40e172e8', 'The workers will ___ a new library in our city next year.', '工人們明年將在我們城市建造一座新圖書館。', 'build', 'cook', 'sing', 'sleep', 'build 為動詞，表示建造、蓋。', '看到 building (建築物) 就想到 build (建造)。', '2026-07-07 08:49:35', '2026-07-07 08:49:35'),
('4e6d22db-6a98-55b7-bd6b-100fb095d804', '4cffd41a-df29-4bc5-ae87-227855083801', 'The heavy ___ holds the boat to the dock.', '這條沉重的纜索將船固定在碼頭上。', 'cable', 'box', 'cup', 'pen', 'cable 指的是纜索。', '想像一條很重的纜索 (cable) 把船固定住。', '2026-07-07 01:57:10', '2026-07-07 01:57:10'),
('03a38045-a2d1-590e-af46-94af43b36858', 'ce164083-0b05-428e-b6d7-e558b8db839c', 'Look up! There is a beautiful lamp hanging from the ___.', '向上看！有一個漂亮的燈掛在天花板上。', 'ceiling', 'floor', 'wall', 'window', 'ceiling 源自於動詞 ceil (覆蓋)，加上字尾 -ing 變成名詞，指覆蓋在房間頂部的部分。', '記住 ceiling fan 就是「吊扇」，吊扇是掛在 ceiling (天花板) 上的。', '2026-07-07 02:48:25', '2026-07-07 02:48:25'),
('1066adc2-edc4-5e9a-ae5c-eeba1371e790', 'e1c0c57b-3447-4e3b-b575-e748a4ad53a9', 'I often play basketball with my ___ after school.', '我放學後經常和我的同班同學一起打籃球。', 'classmate', 'teacher', 'doctor', 'driver', 'class (班級) + mate (夥伴/同伴)', 'class 代表班級，mate 代表夥伴，結合起來就是同班同學。', '2026-07-07 04:26:18', '2026-07-07 04:26:18'),
('77ca06aa-de05-5d62-9626-fffe059cbe8c', '3e74d56a-4b75-4bcc-a8a4-fc010ab5ebc1', 'The ___ in the desert is very hot and dry.', '沙漠裡的氣候非常炎熱且乾燥。', 'climate', 'forest', 'ocean', 'mountain', 'climate 指的是一個地區長期的天氣狀態。', 'climate (氣候) → 記住它是指長期的天氣模式，與當下的天氣 (weather) 不同。', '2026-07-07 04:39:14', '2026-07-07 04:39:14'),
('a4f852d0-c9e3-50a6-b973-67d6c4f10e2c', '9ac93153-0ef7-422d-9821-65f791a3d31e', 'Please ___ the number carefully to call your teacher.', '請仔細地撥打號碼來打給你的老師。', 'dial', 'write', 'read', 'sing', 'dial 作為動詞時，意思是「撥打（電話號碼）」。', '想像在舊式電話上轉動 dial (撥號盤) 來撥號的動作。', '2026-07-07 03:44:59', '2026-07-07 03:44:59'),
('4aecdda2-8805-5092-9f45-eaf86cec02fc', '1f5143d7-50b7-423a-b6bc-b7f67fe6817e', 'After the class, the students had a long ___ about the movie.', '下課後，學生們針對那部電影進行了長久的討論。', 'discussion', 'decision', 'question', 'problem', 'dis- 表示分開，cuss 表示討論，合起來就是討論。', '想像大家把一個話題分開來探討，就是 discussion。', '2026-07-07 04:47:50', '2026-07-07 04:47:50'),
('5ddb8143-e2fe-5c38-8f21-47570e70055c', '885faf35-b997-46e1-a254-139a21ceec21', 'The ___ wind is blowing today.', '今天吹著東風。', 'east', 'cold', 'strong', 'light', 'east (adj.) 在此作為形容詞，表示「東方的」。', 'east (東方) + wind (風) → 東風。', '2026-07-07 03:07:57', '2026-07-07 03:07:57'),
('fb614252-fdf1-5597-a176-a8f0c55983a8', '2a2b1622-df4b-45d7-b3be-b82090cf215a', 'Can you give me an ___ of this word?', '你可以給我這個單字的例子嗎？', 'example', 'idea', 'error', 'image', 'ex (向外) + ample (充足的)', '把充足的資訊向外展示，就是「例子」。', '2026-07-07 05:01:25', '2026-07-07 05:01:25'),
('ee8bfdcc-2d06-560f-b42e-ae7a6db13920', 'ae7296b4-233c-40c7-89e1-604285cd516b', 'The museum is open every day ___ Monday.', '這間博物館每天都開放，除了星期一之外。', 'except', 'since', 'with', 'before', 'ex- (向外) + cept (拿) → 把...拿出去 → 除了...之外', '把某樣東西從清單中「拿走」，就是「除了」的意思', '2026-07-07 05:04:46', '2026-07-07 05:04:46'),
('fc771017-5658-550d-a97a-25b2d2e3222c', '431a2c49-3097-42c0-bd75-44d666eafef3', 'The basketball game was very ___; the fans were shouting and jumping.', '這場籃球比賽非常令人興奮；球迷們都在大喊大叫和跳躍。', 'exciting', 'boring', 'expensive', 'delicious', 'ex (向外) + cite (喚起) + ing (形容詞字尾) → 喚起情緒向外的 → 令人興奮的。', '想像你在看一場激烈的比賽，情緒被 ''向外'' 激發，就是 exciting！', '2026-07-07 05:10:02', '2026-07-07 05:10:02'),
('0aed09f9-3c66-54bb-9ca4-626384234fc0', '25644071-c076-48ce-971c-c0a2267094d6', 'He ___ a student in our class.', '他是我們班上的學生。', 'is', 'loves', 'wants', 'has', 'is 為 be 動詞，用於表示「是」。', 'He, She, It 後面要用 is。', '2026-07-05 08:55:35', '2026-07-05 08:55:35'),
('d75583c9-3211-5099-8254-2f1d18ed666c', '25644071-c076-48ce-971c-c0a2267094d6', 'My sister ___ a teacher.', '我的姊姊是一位老師。', 'is', 'loves', 'wants', 'has', 'is 為 be 動詞，用於表示「是」。', 'He, She, It 後面要用 is。', '2026-07-05 08:55:35', '2026-07-05 08:55:35'),
('5538fc84-54ac-59df-9ea0-5f46c40526bc', '05737cfc-81a1-42b1-9d5d-0c18e7a4370a', 'The important documents are ___ the table in the meeting room.', '重要文件在會議室的桌子上。', 'on', 'in', 'at', 'by', '介系詞，表示在某個物體的表面上。', '想像物體貼在表面上 (on the surface).', '2026-07-05 12:20:47', '2026-07-05 12:20:47'),
('8db66bbd-75e3-5e04-812f-631f8fe5dc68', '8fecc1f7-8571-4e65-874e-7bec724d9609', 'He is ___ most talented musician in the orchestra.', '他是樂團中最有才華的音樂家。', 'the', 'a', 'some', 'any', '定冠詞 (Definite Article)', '形容詞最高級前要加 the', '2026-07-05 10:22:35', '2026-07-05 10:22:35'),
